RWE’s Suewag Unit May Be Bought by German Cities, FTD Reports

-- B y   N i k l a s   M a g n u s s o n
-- 
2011-08-25T16:23:15Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-25/rwe-s-suewag-unit-may-be-bought-by-german-cities-ftd-reports.html
RWE AG (RWE) ’s Suewag unit may be bought
by German municipalities, counties and cities if the company
decides to sell it,  Financial Times Deutschland  reported, citing
regional representatives including Neuwied’s Rainer Kaul.  An acquisition of RWE’s entire 78 percent stake in Suewag
may cost as much as 800 million euros ($1.15 billion), the
newspaper said in a preview of an article that will be published
tomorrow. The rest of the company is already owned by cities and
municipalities, including  Frankfurt , the FTD reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Niklas Magnusson in Hamburg at 
